</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8F8F6511FFB6FFC8C48F02DC942FF9EF" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" type="description">
<paragraph id="C72A369AFFB6FFC8C48F02DC9675FA43" blockId="1.[151,1437,1198,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C48F02DC94F9FB2A" bold="true" box="[151,466,1198,1224]" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Justification of synonymy.</emphasis>
The morphology and copulatory organs of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C7D902DD91FEFB2A" authority="Thorell, 1891" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1891" box="[961,1237,1198,1224]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Zeuxippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C7D902DD911FFB2A" box="[961,1076,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Zeuxippus</emphasis>
Thorell, 1891
</taxonomicName>
appear similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C4F002A094F9FB0E" authority="Thorell, 1869" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1869" box="[232,466,1234,1260]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C4F002A09405FB0E" box="[232,302,1234,1260]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Rhene</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB6FFC8C52E02A094F9FB0E" author="Thorell, T." box="[310,466,1234,1260]" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref8382" refString="Thorell, T. (1869) On European spiders. Part I. Review of the European genera of spiders, preceded by some observations on zoological nomenclature. Nova Acta Regiae Societatis Scientiarum Upsaliensis, Series 3, 7, 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1869">Thorell, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on a detailed comparison of the illustrations of the generotype, 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C0EF02A1944BFAF2" authority="Thorell, 1891" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1891" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Zeuxippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C0EF02A19594FAF2" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Zeuxippus histrio</emphasis>
Thorell, 1891
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB6FFC8C5680284971CFAF2" author="Proszynski, J." box="[368,567,1270,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 177" refId="ref7795" refString="Proszynski, J. (1984) Atlas rysunkow diagnostycznych mniej znanych Salticidae (Araneae). Zeszyty Naukowe Wyzszej Szkoly Rolniczo-Pedagogicznej w Siedlcach, 2, 1 - 177." type="journal article" year="1984">Prószyński, 1984</bibRefCitation>
), it is evident that it has all the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C08F028491F6FAF2" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1869" box="[1175,1245,1270,1296]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C08F028491F6FAF2" box="[1175,1245,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Rhene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as illustrated for 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C48F0368970FFAD7" authority="(C. L. Koch, 1846)" baseAuthorityName="C. L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[151,548,1306,1333]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigera">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C48F03689461FAD6" box="[151,330,1306,1332]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Rhene flavigera</emphasis>
(C.L. 
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB6FFC8C58C03689737FAD7" author="Koch, C. L." box="[404,540,1306,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 234" refId="ref7501" refString="Koch, C. L. (1846) s. n. In: Die Arachniden. Dreizehnter Band &amp; Vierzehnter Band. J. L. Lotzbeck, Nurnberg, pp. 1 - 234, pl. 433 - 468 (f. 1078 - 1271) &amp; pp. 1 - 88, pls. 467 - 480 (f. 1272 - 1342)." type="book chapter" year="1846">Koch, 1846</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The palp with short, curved embolus accompanied by a hook-shaped terminal apophysis; simple pointed RTA; bag-like tegulum and sperm duct of the palp with retromarginal loop are diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C4FC03109401FA9E" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1869" box="[228,298,1378,1404]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C4FC03109401FA9E" box="[228,298,1378,1404]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Rhene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Expect the longer, more obtuse abdomen, characteristic differences in palpal structure are not seen. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C50C03F594ACFA42" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1891" box="[276,391,1415,1440]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Zeuxippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C50C03F594ACFA42" box="[276,391,1415,1440]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Zeuxippus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB6FFC8C70903F4967CFA42" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1869" box="[785,855,1414,1440]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB6FFC8C70903F4967CFA42" box="[785,855,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">Rhene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C72A369AFFB6FFC8C4DF03D8942FF9EF" blockId="1.[151,1437,1198,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="390">
